<TITLE> Korean businesses keen to invest in Bangladesh: Iftekhar Chowdhury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com) South Korean businesses are keen to invest their money in Bangladesh after it signalled a "go ahead" to an exclusive industrial zone for the far-eastern nation, an official statement said Wednesday. The government recently approved setting up of the Korean Export Processing Zone (KEPZ) to attract more investment from the rising Asian economy. Foreign adviser Iftekhar A Chowdhury, who is now in Seoul, said Bangladesh is trying to explore new windows of cooperation with South Korea to boost investment and trade, the statement of the foreign ministry said. Iftekhar is leading a Bangladesh delegation to the Asian Cooperation Ministerial Dialogue in Seoul. He met officials of various Korean government agencies and businesses to discuss mutual benefits. The adviser drew attention of the investors, especially in power and energy sector, to let them know that Bangladesh could be a good destination for better return of their money. Korean businesses showed interest in exploring new sectors in Bangladesh, the statement said. bd
